<span id="v.iii.cxviii-p2"></span><span class="c12"><span
id="v.iii.cxviii-p2.1"></span>Basil</span>, <span
id="fr_2548"></span>[2549](#fn_2548.md) bishop of Cæsarea in Cappadocia,
the city formerly called Mazaca, composed admirable carefully written
books *Against Eunomius,* a volume *On the Holy Spirit,* and nine
homilies *On the six days of creation,* also a work *On asceticism* and
short treatises on various subjects. He died in the reign of Gratianus.

